3@C?
It should show a good second suit, something like KQxxx, Axx, x, KQxx
Another way to think of this is to use Losing Trick Count.
A rebid at the 3 level should be a hand with 6 losers or so
The idea here is that when you bid a new suit at the 2 level. you have a 7- or 8-loser opener, and a new suit at the 3 level is about 1 winner better than that

